author: Haroh Garcia
text: I recently relocated my home gym to this gym, despite living quite far from it. This gym is new, clean, and equipped with the essential machines for a comprehensive daily workout routine. Unlike the nearby AF branches, it doesn‚Äôt get too overcrowded. Additionally, the gym offers complimentary snacks like bread with spreads, which I truly appreciate. One of the standout features is the free Evolt body composition machine, which is available to use anytime, unlike most AF branches where they charge for each scan. Furthermore, this branch boasts the best staff! They are professional and friendly, unlike many other AF branches where the staff consists mainly of part-time staff. I highly recommend this gym to many of my friends, and it never disappoints!

text:

They took the time to explain everything clearly and gave me the confidence I needed to get started. They‚Äôve been incredibly supportive and encouraging, offering guidance whenever I needed it. Overall, I‚Äôm absolutely thrilled with the service and support I‚Äôve received from the team. Joining Anytime Fitness Tekka Place has been a great decision, and I‚Äôm looking forward to my fitness journey with such a dedicated and knowledgeable team behind me! Highly recommend!

author: Rach Ang
text:
Months back I relocated to this branch, the gym is decent and properly maintained, staffs were friendly. Most times they would offer Bread or Bananas which as really nice.

I even renewed my membership with them, but there were some admin glitches. Initially I couldn't tap in, happened for the first 2 times after renewal, possibly due to the renewal of the membership, and then I got hit with late payment fee, even though I have provided the correct card information. When I tried to clarify it on whatsapp, I felt like the staff corresponding with me on whatsapp was avoiding my questions and kept insisting that it was because it was my fault that I pay late. I tried to point out that the last 4 digits of the card that they have keyed into EzPay was wrong (it was 0000). I understand that late payment will result in late payment fee and that is understood in the contract, but this was not the case. Long story short it was acknowledged that they've processed my card details wrongly, but I had to still pay $15 for this mistake.
